19:23.720 --> 19:27.680
Hey... how big is that...
a million dollars?

19:27.760 --> 19:30.400
Does it... does it fit
into a suitcase or, like,
a sack or something?

19:30.520 --> 19:32.477
It's gonna be...
it's gotta be
pretty heavy, right?

19:32.560 --> 19:35.075
Hey, can I...
can I lay in it?

19:35.160 --> 19:36.799
You know,
I always liked
that part of movies

19:36.880 --> 19:38.519
where the characters,
they just lay
in a big pile...

19:38.600 --> 19:39.636
You got a drill?

19:39.760 --> 19:40.796
Yeah.

19:41.920 --> 19:43.832
And then they always...
they always take the money,

19:43.920 --> 19:45.832
and they just, like,
throw it up in the air,

19:45.920 --> 19:48.116
and the money just...

19:48.200 --> 19:50.795
just, like, flutters down
on top of them, you know?

19:50.880 --> 19:53.076
God damn.
We're doing this.
We're really...

19:54.160 --> 19:55.150
I got goose bumps.

19:55.240 --> 19:56.310
Wood screws.

19:56.440 --> 19:57.510
Yeah.

19:57.600 --> 20:01.514
I'm gonna buy real
marble for the spa.
6 inches thick.

20:02.280 --> 20:05.751
I got these...
I got these
French lotions on hold.

20:05.840 --> 20:07.559
They smell like sunflowers.

20:08.640 --> 20:09.710
Uh, these?

20:10.440 --> 20:11.715
Longer.
Okay.

20:11.800 --> 20:12.995
So what do we...
what do we do?

20:13.080 --> 20:14.196
Just, like,
call him in the morning,

20:14.280 --> 20:16.397
you know,
tell him where to meet us?

20:16.480 --> 20:17.550
I don't know, these?

20:17.680 --> 20:18.796
Yeah, give me a few.

