Look at me.
I'm sweating.

20:20.640 --> 20:23.075
Here. Oh, man.

20:23.200 --> 20:28.070
Hey... do I get to
use that voice thing again?

20:28.160 --> 20:30.834
You know, the...
the Darth Vader,
super sinister, like,

20:30.920 --> 20:32.832
"Luke, I am your father."

20:32.960 --> 20:33.950
Please step in.

20:34.040 --> 20:35.030
Sure.

20:37.120 --> 20:40.113
Hey, you know, I...
I never even asked you,

20:40.200 --> 20:42.317
what are you gonna do
with your share of the money?

20:42.400 --> 20:44.995
I mean,
I told you about my...

20:46.440 --> 20:47.430
Uh...

20:47.880 --> 20:50.952
Yeah, am I...
Did you mean to
lock me in here?

20:51.040 --> 20:52.759
We got a big day tomorrow.
Get some rest.

20:52.840 --> 20:56.880
I don't want you
getting cold feet.
I'll see you in the morning.

20:56.960 --> 21:00.795
No, no, wait.
Hold on now. Heck, I'm...

21:01.680 --> 21:03.080
What am I supposed to...

21:03.160 --> 21:05.629
What... what if I
gotta go to the toilet?

21:05.720 --> 21:08.474
You're a smart guy.
You'll figure something out.

21:14.520 --> 21:15.510
Poop.

21:44.440 --> 21:46.272
I have news.

21:46.360 --> 21:48.556
It's just slowing
down at the shop.

21:50.000 --> 21:50.990
Lester?

21:51.120 --> 21:52.952
It's not my fault.

21:53.080 --> 21:55.834
You bought me...
you bought me the tie.

21:56.560 --> 21:58.074
You... You...

22:07.840 --> 22:09.240
Is it a cut or what is it?

22:09.320 --> 22:11.835
Puncture, maybe.
Hard to tell
with all the gore.

22:12.720 --> 22:14.393
Mr. Nygaard,
can you hear me?

22:15.400 --> 22:18.199
It's the towel sound.
She's washing towels.

22:19.040 --> 22:21.794
Mr. Nygaard,
we're getting you
to the hospital.

22:21.880 --> 22:23.075
What happened to your hand?

22:23.160 --> 22:24.196
Socks.

22:24.360 --> 22:25.396
What about socks?

22:25.480 --> 22:28.871
For $55 he threw
in the shotgun.

22:30.000 --> 22:32.276
I don't understand.
Were you shot?

22:36.000 --> 22:36.990
Mr. Nygaard.

22:40.680 --> 22:43.036
Did you pay Lorne Malvo
to kill Sam Hess?

22:44.040 --> 22:45.872
I never paid him.

22:46.760 --> 22:48.797
Okay, offered to pay then.

22:48.880 --> 22:51.793
Made a deal.
And then... when he
came for the money...

22:51.880 --> 22:54.793
I never paid.
I didn't pay.

22:55.640 --> 22:56.869
Yeah, okay, but...

22:56.960 --> 23:01.113
arrangements were made...
and then...

23:01.200 --> 23:02.873
I don't know,
you tell me,
things went south--

23:02.960 --> 23:03.916
Excuse us, miss.

23:04.000 --> 23:05.673
There...

23:06.680 --> 23:07.796
There.

23:07.920 --> 23:09.036
All right,
we'll get you inside.

23:09.120 --> 23:11.919
Of course.
Left right there.

23:44.040 --> 23:45.554
Is that what
you're looking for then?

24:44.680 --> 24:45.955
Two kids.

24:46.720 --> 24:47.915
I'm sorry?

24:49.560 --> 24:53.110
I got two kids and a wife
who thinks out loud.

24:53.880 --> 24:55.234
This is the time I get.

24:56.720 --> 24:58.951
Accidental for me.

24:59.760 --> 25:01.160
Troubled mind.

25:02.320 --> 25:03.754
I'll come to you.

25:15.080 --> 25:18.278
The winters are cold...
but I can't complain.

25:20.520 --> 25:24.309
My socks have holes...
but again, do I complain?

25:24.400 --> 25:25.390
I do not.

25:27.360 --> 25:30.194
The oldest needs braces...

25:30.280 --> 25:33.796
the youngest once sneezed
for three days straight...

25:35.400 --> 25:37.278
but who could complain?

25:37.360 --> 25:38.635
They're gifts.

25:39.360 --> 25:40.396
Children?

25:40.520 --> 25:41.556
All of it.

25:42.280 --> 25:44.272
The cold, the holes.

25:49.280 --> 25:52.193
Hey, so...
I have a question.

25:52.320 --> 25:54.471
Spiritually, I mean.
Um...

25:54.560 --> 25:56.313
Or not spiritually, but...

25:56.400 --> 26:00.235
I don't know, of...
like, an ethical nature.

26:00.960 --> 26:01.950
Please.

26:03.960 --> 26:05.189
Well...

26:07.320 --> 26:09.516
let's say I know
a person is guilty.

26:09.600 --> 26:14.072
He's committed a crime,
only... you know...
I can't prove it.

26:16.000 --> 26:19.357
Like, he has
everyone else fooled,
but... but I know.

26:20.960 --> 26:21.950
What am I--

26:22.040 --> 26:23.235
Find the proof.

26:23.320 --> 26:26.711
Yeah... okay,
but here's the thing...

26:26.800 --> 26:28.837
I'm no detective.

26:30.520 --> 26:33.240
I mean, Molly, she's...

26:33.360 --> 26:34.589
amazing.

26:34.680 --> 26:36.160
But I just...

26:37.720 --> 26:40.599
And then there's Greta,
you know, and... and...

26:40.680 --> 26:43.991
Am I supposed to
put myself in danger
or do I just...

26:45.360 --> 26:48.671
I don't know,
just... let it go?

26:52.760 --> 26:55.195
A rich man opens
the paper one day.

26:56.160 --> 26:58.277
He sees the world
is full of misery.

26:58.360 --> 26:59.555
Is this a...

26:59.720 --> 27:00.915
It's a parable.

27:02.440 --> 27:04.750
A rich man opens
the paper one day.

27:04.840 --> 27:07.355
He sees the world
is full of misery.

27:08.720 --> 27:10.552
<i>He says...</i>

27:10.640 --> 27:12.996
<i>"I have money.
I can help."</i>

27:15.200 --> 27:18.750
<i>So, he gives away
all of his money...</i>

27:23.200 --> 27:25.271
<i>but it's not enough.</i>

27:25.360 --> 27:27.636
<i>The people are
still suffering.</i>

27:31.680 --> 27:33.558
<i>One day the man
sees another article.</i>

27:36.440 --> 27:41.595
<i>He decides he was
foolish to think just
giving money was enough.</i>

27:41.720 --> 27:43.518
<i>So, he goes to
the doctor and says,</i>

27:43.680 --> 27:45.512
<i>"Doctor, I want to
donate a kidney."</i>

27:47.720 --> 27:50.076
<i>The doctors do the surgery.</i>

27:51.760 --> 27:53.717
<i>It's a complete success.</i>

27:58.080 --> 28:01.517
<i>After, he knows
he should feel good,
but he doesn't...</i>

28:02.680 --> 28:04.956
<i>for people are
still suffering.</i>

28:07.440 --> 28:10.399
<i>So he goes back
to the doctor.</i>

28:10.480 --> 28:14.599
<i>He says, "Doctor,
this time, I want
to give it all."</i>

28:15.760 --> 28:18.195
<i>The doctor says,
"What does that mean,
give it all?"</i>

28:18.280 --> 28:21.398
<i>He says, "This time,
I want to donate my liver...</i>

28:21.480 --> 28:23.119
but not just my liver.

28:23.200 --> 28:25.715
I want to donate my heart,
but not just my heart.

28:25.800 --> 28:28.793
I want to donate my corneas,
but not just my corneas.

28:28.880 --> 28:31.111
<i>I want to
give it all away...</i>

28:32.080 --> 28:33.719
<i>everything I am...</i>

28:33.800 --> 28:35.473
<i>all that I have."</i>

28:36.640 --> 28:38.074
<i>The doctor says,</i>

28:38.160 --> 28:39.674
<i>"A kidney is one thing,</i>

28:39.760 --> 28:42.639
<i>but you can't give away
your whole body,
piece by piece.</i>

28:42.720 --> 28:43.915
<i>That's suicide."</i>

28:44.880 --> 28:46.473
<i>And he sends the man home.</i>

28:50.760 --> 28:53.400
<i>But the man cannot live...</i>

28:53.480 --> 28:58.111
<i>knowing that
the people are suffering
and he could help.</i>

28:59.880 --> 29:02.600
<i>So he gives the one
thing he has left...</i>

29:03.560 --> 29:04.550
<i>his life.</i>

29:12.560 --> 29:15.519
<i>And does it work?
Does it stop the suffering?</i>

29:17.000 --> 29:19.720
You live in the world.
What do you think?

29:20.720 --> 29:23.599
So, he killed
himself for nothing?

29:23.680 --> 29:24.830
Did he?

29:25.760 --> 29:27.319
Well, I mean...

29:29.880 --> 29:31.519
You're saying...

29:35.800 --> 29:37.519
What are you saying?

29:38.280 --> 29:41.591
Only a fool thinks
he can solve
the world's problems.

29:43.680 --> 29:46.195
Yeah, but you gotta
try, don't you?

30:09.200 --> 30:10.270
Nope.

30:57.720 --> 30:58.995
Keep it running.

31:18.280 --> 31:20.556
Say, Dad...

31:20.640 --> 31:23.553
I was talking
to the, uh, bug guy.

31:23.640 --> 31:25.711
He's saying this
is all real odd.

31:25.800 --> 31:30.079
The crickets...
he's saying they're
not local, you know...

31:30.200 --> 31:31.634
not from around here.

31:31.720 --> 31:32.710
He's saying
they're the kind

31:32.800 --> 31:34.996
you buy at a pet store
to feed your lizard or...

31:35.120 --> 31:36.076
God sent them.

31:36.160 --> 31:39.073
Yeah... but, well...

31:39.160 --> 31:42.232
So... I called around
to all the pet stores,

31:42.320 --> 31:43.470
and wouldn't you know--

31:43.560 --> 31:45.313
Look, kid,
I don't have
time for this now.

31:45.400 --> 31:47.357
Just clean it up.
Then pack your shit.

31:47.440 --> 31:49.272
Wally is coming
to take you to the cabin.

31:49.360 --> 31:50.555
Yeah, but, Dad...
No buts!

31:50.640 --> 31:52.871
Just do it.

32:09.400 --> 32:10.720
Excuse me.

32:14.600 --> 32:15.920
Hey there, Molly.

32:16.040 --> 32:17.190
Hey.

32:17.280 --> 32:18.430
Uh, Lester okay?

32:18.520 --> 32:20.989
He's had a bad week,
that's for sure.
Yeah.

32:21.080 --> 32:22.878
What's this?
His third time in?
Yeah.

32:23.000 --> 32:25.913
On the plus side,
the nose is healing nicely.

32:26.000 --> 32:27.673
Well, that's a start.
Yeah.

32:29.120 --> 32:31.635
So... Uh, listen,
about that hand...

32:31.760 --> 32:33.114
Oh, real mess there.

32:33.200 --> 32:35.669
Super infected, nasty stuff.

32:35.760 --> 32:38.434
I drained the wound,
removed the foreign object,

32:38.560 --> 32:42.634
cut away the necrotic tissue,
and filled him full
of IV antibiotics.

32:42.720 --> 32:44.632
He won't lose the hand,
but it came close.

32:44.720 --> 32:47.519
Yeah. Now, when you say...
foreign object...

32:47.600 --> 32:49.193
Shotgun pellet,
looked like.

32:49.320 --> 32:50.800
Had some fabric
attached to it.

32:50.880 --> 32:53.315
So, it's possible the pellet
passed through something

32:53.400 --> 32:56.199
before getting
into Lester's hand.

32:56.280 --> 32:57.760
Yeah, or someone.

32:57.840 --> 32:59.593
Pardon?

32:59.680 --> 33:00.670
Can I talk to him?

33:00.760 --> 33:01.750
Well, he's sedated now,

33:01.840 --> 33:04.674
on account of
he was septic when
you brought him in, so...

33:04.760 --> 33:06.194
Like I said,
real nasty stuff.

33:06.320 --> 33:07.720
Right, yeah, yeah.

33:07.800 --> 33:09.712
Be a while before
he can answer any questions.

33:09.840 --> 33:11.240
Hey, you seen Ida?

33:12.320 --> 33:13.310
Wait, is she here?

33:13.400 --> 33:16.472
Yeah... upstairs.
Just had the baby.

33:16.560 --> 33:18.313
Holy smokes.
Yeah.

33:18.400 --> 33:19.390
Girl or boy?

33:20.560 --> 33:24.349
Bernadette,
I heard, so... girl.

33:25.280 --> 33:26.873
Yeah.
Yeah.

33:26.960 --> 33:29.236
<i>Dr. Esbit, call 1 18.</i>

33:29.360 --> 33:31.317
Excuse me.
All right.

37:07.800 --> 37:09.951
It was the Romans,
wasn't it?

37:14.080 --> 37:15.753
What are you saying?

37:15.840 --> 37:19.550
Saint Lawrence, your window...
the Romans burned him alive.

37:21.120 --> 37:23.077
They did?

37:23.160 --> 37:24.150
You know why?

37:25.040 --> 37:27.236
'Cause he was Christian.

37:27.320 --> 37:28.993
Maybe.

37:30.720 --> 37:34.680
But I think it was
because the Romans
were raised by wolves.

37:36.000 --> 37:39.676
Greatest empire
in human history,
founded by wolves.

37:42.400 --> 37:44.357
You know what wolves do.

37:45.720 --> 37:47.712
They hunt.

37:48.520 --> 37:49.840
They kill.

37:51.840 --> 37:54.435
That's why I never bought
into <i>The Jungle Book.</i>

37:54.520 --> 37:55.795
A boy is raised by wolves,

37:55.880 --> 37:58.634
he becomes friends
with a bear and a panther.

37:58.720 --> 38:00.279
I don't think so.

38:05.560 --> 38:09.440
I knew a guy once.
Had a 110-pound Rottweiler...

38:09.520 --> 38:11.432
and one night,
this girl thought
it'd be funny

38:11.520 --> 38:14.718
to get down on all fours
and let the dog hump her.

38:15.800 --> 38:17.917
The dog still
had its balls.

38:18.880 --> 38:22.430
Well, the dog gets up there,
but he's not in on the joke.

38:23.880 --> 38:27.032
This is just a bitch in heat
as far as he's concerned...

38:27.120 --> 38:30.397
and he's not leaving till
he gets what he came for.

38:31.760 --> 38:35.470
Well, the girl, too late,
realizes the kind of
mistake she's made.

38:35.560 --> 38:37.313
She wants to get up.

38:39.080 --> 38:41.197
But the dog had other ideas.

38:44.880 --> 38:47.554
Had to shoot it
behind the ear to
get it off of her.

38:51.080 --> 38:52.992
I don't... I don't...

38:53.080 --> 38:55.072
Well, I'm saying that...

38:55.160 --> 38:57.277
the Romans,
raised by wolves,

38:57.360 --> 39:00.671
they see a guy
turning water into wine...

39:00.760 --> 39:01.830
what do they do?

39:01.920 --> 39:03.400
They eat him.

39:04.760 --> 39:08.356
'Cause there are no saints
in the animal kingdom.

39:08.440 --> 39:10.432
Only breakfast and dinner.

40:09.280 --> 40:11.590
So what time do
you want me to pick
you up in the morning?

40:11.720 --> 40:14.440
No... we're done.

40:14.520 --> 40:16.671
You can stay the night,
but you gotta hit
the road come dawn.

40:17.800 --> 40:19.678
Here's what I owe you.

40:21.480 --> 40:23.472
Sorry it didn't work out.

40:54.600 --> 40:55.875
Grimly.

40:55.960 --> 40:58.680
<i>Heya... it's Molly.</i>

40:58.760 --> 41:00.399
Oh, yeah,
how you doin' there?

41:00.520 --> 41:02.159
Pretty good.

41:02.240 --> 41:03.799
How's things
going with you?

41:03.880 --> 41:08.477
Not bad. Just...
trying to figure
this thing out.

41:08.560 --> 41:10.677
Yeah, so,
I was wondering...

41:10.760 --> 41:12.353
with this fella
I arrested...

41:13.520 --> 41:17.150
how come he was there,
you know, on the street...

41:17.240 --> 41:18.310
on that street?

41:18.400 --> 41:20.392
I mean,
if he is our guy and not,

41:20.480 --> 41:22.551
you know,
some pastor actually.

41:23.800 --> 41:25.029
<i>So what'd
you come up with?</i>

41:25.120 --> 41:26.918
Well, see...

41:27.000 --> 41:30.072
I'm not sure
what I'm looking
for is the problem.

41:30.160 --> 41:34.632
Plus, you know,
it's dark out, so...
maybe go back out tomorrow.

41:34.760 --> 41:37.036
Oh. I was thinking
I might drive
out in the morning,

41:37.120 --> 41:38.395
take a look at Lester's car.

41:39.240 --> 41:42.836
Thought maybe...
after we could get together.

41:42.920 --> 41:44.149
You know,
compare notes on this thing.

41:45.320 --> 41:48.119
Sure. That'd be...

41:48.200 --> 41:49.475
I'd like that.

41:51.080 --> 41:52.355
Okay, so tomorrow then.

41:53.080 --> 41:54.230
Okay.

42:21.080 --> 42:23.356
<i>What'd you get
for number three?</i>

42:23.440 --> 42:26.114
<i>X squared.
What'd you get for four?</i>

42:28.120 --> 42:29.839
<i>A rhombus?</i>

42:41.560 --> 42:42.596
Help you?

42:42.680 --> 42:44.478
You're not
supposed to be here.

42:45.360 --> 42:48.797
Oh, no, I'm pretty sure
I'm right where
I'm supposed to be.

43:02.640 --> 43:03.960
Hi.

43:04.040 --> 43:05.360
Neighborhood watch.

43:05.440 --> 43:07.397
If you don't move,
I'm gonna have
to call the cops.

43:07.520 --> 43:09.591
Well, friend,
there's no need for that.

43:09.680 --> 43:11.876
This is a nice neighborhood.

43:11.960 --> 43:14.839
Children play in
the streets, my children.

43:14.920 --> 43:18.152
We have block parties...
fruit punch.

43:18.280 --> 43:21.956
We don't need a man
in a dark car doing things.

43:22.800 --> 43:24.280
You mean like sitting?

43:24.360 --> 43:25.714
Don't be a <i>nudnik.</i>

43:25.800 --> 43:27.917
This is a community.

43:28.040 --> 43:30.236
People watch
each other's backs.

43:30.320 --> 43:33.074
Someone gets sick,
someone dies,
you bring a casserole...

43:33.160 --> 43:34.150
help.

43:34.880 --> 43:36.439
Maybe I'm here to help.

43:36.520 --> 43:38.318
No, you have black eyes.

43:38.400 --> 43:39.436
You're trouble.

43:39.520 --> 43:41.955
I'm going inside
and I'm calling the cops.

43:42.040 --> 43:43.076
Which building?

43:43.880 --> 43:46.031
The one with
the Jew bus outside?

43:47.200 --> 43:49.112
There it is.

43:49.200 --> 43:50.714
Now the truth comes out.

43:51.680 --> 43:54.036
You know...
some people think

43:54.120 --> 43:57.796
you don't need alarms
on second story windows.

43:57.880 --> 44:01.430
They think they
can save a few bucks,
you know, and still be safe.

44:02.560 --> 44:03.789
Another way they save money

44:03.880 --> 44:07.556
is they don't
hook up the alarm
to the phone line,

44:07.640 --> 44:10.633
so the bell rings,
but the cops don't come...

44:11.560 --> 44:14.712
or they come,
but only after
the neighbors call...

44:15.840 --> 44:20.039
which... if this community
is tight as you say,

44:20.120 --> 44:21.520
you know...

44:23.080 --> 44:26.517
just might be quick enough
to save your life...

44:26.640 --> 44:29.235
or your children's lives...

44:29.320 --> 44:30.595
maybe.

44:31.840 --> 44:33.240
Se'irim.

44:34.320 --> 44:36.198
You have a nice night.

45:12.280 --> 45:13.714
How come we're all
in the hall then?

45:13.800 --> 45:16.634
Ida kicked us out...
said we were being too loud.

45:16.720 --> 45:19.030
Ah. You know,
she did just
have a baby, so...

45:19.120 --> 45:20.474
Ah. We all agreed it
was a good point.

45:20.640 --> 45:21.960
Yeah.

45:24.800 --> 45:27.599
So you're... being loud
in the hall instead.

45:29.960 --> 45:32.236
All right, boys,
let's... pack it up.

45:32.320 --> 45:33.549
Call her a night.

45:33.640 --> 45:35.677
You really wanna go out there?
No.

45:35.760 --> 45:36.910
Goin' away.
From me.

45:37.000 --> 45:38.559
I gotta protect
the baby here.

45:38.640 --> 45:40.438
Come on...
Bill's got a job to do.

45:40.520 --> 45:42.989
Hey, you're making
too much noise.

45:48.200 --> 45:50.237
Sorry, you sleeping?

45:57.840 --> 46:00.435
Well,
that's a baby, all right.

46:00.520 --> 46:01.840
Smell her.

46:04.320 --> 46:05.310
Okay.

46:13.520 --> 46:15.034
That's what a new
one smells like then.

46:15.120 --> 46:16.190
Yeah.

46:17.680 --> 46:19.160
How you holding up?

46:19.240 --> 46:20.276
Me?

46:20.360 --> 46:22.272
You're the one
just had a baby.

46:22.360 --> 46:23.874
Yeah, but I get
to lie down now.

46:24.040 --> 46:25.520
Yeah.

46:26.440 --> 46:28.272
I just look tired.

46:28.360 --> 46:30.113
Inside, I'm raring to go.

46:35.040 --> 46:36.679
So...

46:39.040 --> 46:40.793
How much do you wanna--
I don't need details.

46:40.880 --> 46:42.872
Just tell me
you're taking care of it.

46:44.280 --> 46:45.873
I'm trying, yeah.

46:53.640 --> 46:55.711
Do you want me
to stay the night?
I could sleep in the chair.

46:55.800 --> 46:57.120
No, I got people coming...

46:57.200 --> 47:00.113
my sister and her daughter.

47:00.200 --> 47:02.192
Be here around
11:00, she said.

47:03.080 --> 47:05.993
They said... Bernadette.

47:06.080 --> 47:08.515
Vern's idea...
his mother's name.

47:09.240 --> 47:11.471
I wanted Allie.

47:11.560 --> 47:14.234
And now he's dead.

47:14.320 --> 47:16.232
That man always knew
how to win an argument.

47:19.960 --> 47:21.314
I think it's pretty, so...

47:21.440 --> 47:23.909
Good 'cause
you're the babysitter.

47:26.320 --> 47:28.676
Now go home.
Let me sleep.

47:28.760 --> 47:30.877
And you do the same.
You look like a raccoon.

47:30.960 --> 47:33.191
Yeah.

47:33.280 --> 47:36.239
I gotta go to
Duluth in the a.m.,
but I'll stop by after, yeah.
